---
const steps = [
	{
		title: '1. Quick kickoff call',
		body: 'You tell us what you do, where you serve, and what kind of jobs you want more of.',
	},
	{
		title: '2. First draft in week one',
		body: 'You get a full walkthrough of your new website in week one so changes can be made early.',
	},
	{
		title: '3. Build and dial it in',
		body: 'We finish the site, write strong sales copy, and set up local SEO basics so customers can find you.',
	},
	{
		title: '4. Launch in about two weeks',
		body: 'Once approved, we launch your site and manage everything moving forward so you can stay focused on jobs.',
	},
];
---

<section class="layout-section">
	<div class="layout-container">
		<div class="mb-10 max-w-3xl">
			<p class="text-eyebrow">Delivery Process</p>
			<h2 class="mt-2">No runaround. Clear steps. Fast launch.</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
				You always know what is happening, what we need from you, and when your site goes live. <strong>We keep you posted on any issues, handle any technical problems, and check-in frequently post-launch to ensure everything is working exactly the way you want.</strong>
			</p>
		</div>
		<ol class="m-0 grid list-none gap-4 p-0 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
			{
				steps.map((step) => (
					<li class="card-surface flex flex-col gap-2">
						<h3>{step.title}</h3>
						<p class="m-0 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">{step.body}</p>
					</li>
				))
			}
		</ol>
	</div>
</section>
